    <section class='mbx'>
        <h2 id='snapsat'>Snapsat</h2>
        <p>In the past, creating a custom Landsat 8 composite has required that users download the entirety of the scene they were interested in, configure the tools required to process them, and then hope that the output they got was what they intended to reproduce. Snapsat was created as a means of simplifying that process. Users are able to rapidly preview scenes and download full-size renders without having to take the time to download or configure anything.</p>
        <p>Creating a composite with Snapsat requires 4 simple steps:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Select the location you're interested in.</li>
            <li>Select the date you're interested in.</li>
            <li>Preview your selection to make sure it's what you want.</li>
            <li>Download it.</li>
        </ol>
